  "text": "**Prometheus/prometheus**: Tracer initialization lives in `tracing/tracing.go` where `Manager.ApplyConfig` calls `buildTracerProvider` to create an `tracesdk.NewTracerProvider` and installs it globally via `otel.SetTracerProvider`. Spans are created throughout the codebase using `otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, name)` \u2014 in `storage/remote/client.go` (Remote Store/Read), `storage/remote/queue_manager.go` (batch sends with attributes and RecordError), `scrape/scrape.go` (Scrape spans), `rules/group.go` (rule evaluation), `promql/engine.go` (query eval with SetAttributes), and `util/stats/query_stats.go` (SpanTimer utility that wraps Start/End). Prometheus uses `span.SetAttributes` for metadata, `span.RecordError` for error recording, and `defer span.End()` for span completion.\n\n**Grafana/grafana**: Tracer initialization is in `pkg/infra/tracing/tracing.go` where `TracingService.initOpentelemetryTracer` selects between Jaeger/OTLP/noop exporters, builds a TracerProvider via `initTracerProvider` (using `tracesdk.NewTracerProvider`), sets it globally with `otel.SetTracerProvider`, and obtains the tracer via `otel.GetTracerProvider().Tracer(\"component-main\")`. The `Tracer` interface (extending `trace.Tracer`) is defined in both `pkg/infra/tracing/tracing.go` and `pkg/plugins/tracing/tracing.go`. Spans are started via `tracer.Start(ctx, name)` throughout \u2014 in expr/, tsdb/loki/, tsdb/tempo/, tsdb/graphite/, tsdb/parca/, api/, bus/, services/. Error recording uses a centralized `Error()` helper (in both `pkg/infra/tracing/tracing.go` and `pkg/plugins/tracing/tracing.go`) that calls `span.SetStatus(codes.Error, ...)` + `span.RecordError(err)`. The `pkg/modules/tracing/listener.go` shows lifecycle span management with SetAttributes, SetStatus, and RecordError for service state transitions.",
